• Take a walk near Lake Nyinawumuntu in Rwanda and you will witness a rare spectacle. A hundred turtles gather around the lakeside. This involves instincts as much as it is on account of a hunger for snails, which are abundant in this region.

The present day relevance of Rwanda

The main concern by Rwandans, according to the information on the website of their government, is “peace”. Their vision is of a Rwanda with “a prosperous and integrated society” by the year 2020. When I mix the need for peace with the motto of all Rwandans: “we cannot go back”, (as in, we all suffered enough, and it’s never going to happen again), I find the Rwandans are secondary to the interests of international corporations and the foreigner-partners who so generously pretend to aid them.
